# mqtt-parse smoke: MQTT v3.1.1 + v5.0 control packet decoding.
# Hex literals in smoke.sql are pre-built valid frames covering
# PUBLISH (QoS0 / QoS1+retain+pid), CONNECT (v3.1.1), PINGREQ,
# SUBSCRIBE, plus a few sad-path cases (garbage bytes -> 0/NULL,
# NULL input -> NULL). Last row asserts mqtt_version() prefix.
PUBLISH
a/b
0
0
<NULL>
hi
1
PUBLISH
1
1
4660
hello
CONNECT
1
PINGREQ
1
SUBSCRIBE
1
<NULL>
0
<NULL>
<NULL>
PUBLISH
a/b
0
hi
1
